item.title: [508]::players command[508]
item.dc:creator: @Owned_Pl0xs Owned_Pl0xs
item.description:
@Owned_Pl0xs wrote:

[quote=“Slave Scyth, post:6, topic:324142”][quote author=Owned_Pl0xs link=topic=420543.msg3089206#msg3089206 date=1262744095]

[code] if (cmd[0].equals(“player”)) {
p.getActionSender().sendMessage(p, “There are currently “+Server.engine.getPlayerCount()+” players online.”);
int number = 0;
for (Player p5 : Engine.players) {
if(p5 == null)
continue;
number++;
switch(p.rights) {
case 0:
p.getActionSender().setString(p, “(”+p5.playerId+")[Player] “+p5.username+” Combat: "+p5.combatLevel, 275, (11+number));
break;

			case 1:
				if (p.donator == 1) {
					p.getActionSender().setString(p, "("+p5.playerId+")<shad=787878>[Moderator & Donator]<img=0> "+p5.username+" Combat: "+p5.combatLevel, 275, (11+number));
				} else {
					p.getActionSender().setString(p, "("+p5.playerId+")<shad=787878>[Moderator]<img=0> "+p5.username+" Combat: "+p5.combatLevel, 275, (11+number));
				}
			break;

			case 2:
				if (p.donator == 1) {
					p.getActionSender().setString(p, "("+p5.playerId+")<shad=ffff00>[Administrator & Donator]<img=1> "+p5.username+" Combat: "+p5.combatLevel, 275, (11+number));
				} else {
					p.getActionSender().setString(p, "("+p5.playerId+")<shad=ffff00>[Administrator]<img=1> "+p5.username+" Combat: "+p5.combatLevel, 275, (11+number));
				}
			break;
                            default:
                                            p.getActionSender().setString(p, "("+p5.playerId+")<shad=ffff00>[Other]<img=1> "+p5.username+" Combat: "+p5.combatLevel, 275, (11+number));
                            break;
		}
	   	p.getActionSender().setString(p, "Neva-PVP[508] Players", 275, 10);
	   	p.getActionSender().setString(p, "Players Online: "+number, 275, 11);
	   	p.getActionSender().setOverlay(p, 275);
	   	p.getActionSender().setString(p, "Player's Online", 275, 2);
	   }
	}[/code]

[/quote]
Owned was right on… but with switch statements, it’s best to have a default option as well; just in case, for whatever reason, an unexpected value pops up.[/quote]

I didn’t think it’d be necessary considering he didn’t really have anything in there for any other values except 0 1 and 2, so if he didn’t go with the switch statement, either way the unexcepted values such as less than 0 or more than 2 might pop up and he rather not go with it because the unexpected values could just be used as hidden players so they aren’t shown on the list, which is actually a bright idea for undercover admins etc…, and could be nulls.
